# Text-Muted Rule

- **Main Rule**: NEVER use the `text-muted` Bootstrap utility class in this project. Use opacity utilities or appropriate text color classes instead.

- **Problem:**
  - `text-muted` applies a light gray color (`#6c757d` in Bootstrap) that has poor contrast on dark backgrounds
  - This creates accessibility issues and poor readability
  - Dark backgrounds require lighter text colors, not muted gray

- **Solution:**
  - Use `opacity-75` or `opacity-50` utilities instead - these maintain the base text color while reducing opacity
  - For dark backgrounds, use `text-white` or `text-light` with opacity utilities
  - For light backgrounds, use opacity utilities on default text color

- **Examples:**

  ```html
  <!-- ❌ DON'T: Never use text-muted -->
  <div class="bg-dark">
      <p class="text-muted">This is hard to read</p>
  </div>
  
  <div class="card bg-primary text-white">
      <p class="text-muted">Poor contrast here</p>
  </div>
  
  <!-- ✅ DO: Use opacity utilities -->
  <div class="bg-dark">
      <p class="text-white opacity-75">Readable on dark</p>
  </div>
  
  <div class="card bg-primary text-white">
      <p class="opacity-75">Good contrast</p>
  </div>
  
  <!-- ✅ DO: opacity on light backgrounds -->
  <div class="card">
      <p class="opacity-75">Subtle text on light background</p>
  </div>
  ```

- **When to Use:**
  - **Light backgrounds**: Use `opacity-75` or `opacity-50` on default text color
  - **Dark backgrounds**: Use `text-white` or `text-light` with `opacity-75` or `opacity-50`
  - **Colored backgrounds**: Use appropriate text color class (`text-white`, `text-light`) with opacity utilities

- **Bootstrap Alternatives:**
  - `opacity-75` - 75% opacity (subtle)
  - `opacity-50` - 50% opacity (more subtle)
  - `opacity-25` - 25% opacity (very subtle)
  - `text-white` - White text for dark backgrounds
  - `text-light` - Light gray text for dark backgrounds

- **Accessibility:**
  - Always ensure sufficient contrast ratio (WCAG AA minimum 4.5:1 for normal text)
  - Test text readability on both light and dark backgrounds
  - Use browser dev tools to check contrast ratios

- **Enforcement:**
  - NEVER use `text-muted` in this project
  - Replace any existing instances with appropriate opacity or text color utilities
  - Verify contrast ratios meet accessibility standards
